  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Social Media Marketing Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>We’re Hiring: Social Media Marketing Assistant</strong></p><p>Are you the friend who’s always spotting new trends before they blow up?<br />Do you love turning creative ideas into scroll-stopping posts?</p><p>If yes, you might be the perfect fit for our team.</p><p>Join us for a hands-on role that blends creativity, strategy, and real-world impact — all within the finance industry, where you’ll help transform complex topics into fun, relatable content people actually <em>want</em> to consume.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conceptualise and produce engaging content for platforms like Instagram and TikTok</li><li>Plan and execute campaigns that make finance simple, digestible, and exciting</li><li>Build and manage a content calendar to grow reach and boost engagement</li><li>Support photoshoots and assist with photo/video editing and basic graphic or web design</li><li>Track performance metrics, analyse insights, and pitch fresh ideas to elevate content</li></ul><p><strong>Who We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li>GCE A Levels or a Local Diploma</li><li>Proficiency in creative tools (Photoshop, Premiere Pro, Adobe Suite, or similar)</li><li>Prior experience in content creation or marketing is a plus</li><li>Creative, curious, and always eager to try new ideas</li><li>Strong attention to detail with a good eye for visuals and storytelling</li></ul><p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><ul><li>Real opportunities for growth, learning, and career development</li><li>A fun, supportive team that celebrates creativity and initiative</li><li>Competitive salary with performance-based incentives</li><li>Travel and exposure opportunities</li><li>Practical insight into the finance industry while building a strong digital marketing portfolio</li></ul><p>If you’re ready to create meaningful content, sharpen your skills, and make an impact — we’d love to hear from you.</p>",
